Originally, I was going to write a "cautiously optimistic" review thinking that this place had just opened! However, as I am reviewing other reviews, they have been at this for well over a year.  Not sure who is managing or owns this place but customer service, communications and accuracy ARE NOT any of the top 5 priorities at this joint.  First, if you have not been there, note that this is a "take-out only" place with no proper signage! It sits (or leases space) inside of another restaurant called Hangar Pub & Grill. While the help at WOW tell you that you can eat there, the waitresses at the bar are disgusted and not accommodating when you tell them you were told you could sit there. Its been 2 years folks, figure it out! Stop telling people you can order wings and then go sit at someone else's restaurant!  Second, ALWAYS CHECK YOUR ORDER BEFORE YOU LEAVE. Apparently, reading English as opposed to speaking English is not a requirement of the kitchen. Not a single non American on site, all home grown English speaking folks who could not read a simple order of plain wings. That's pathetic.  You might argue, oh maybe it was a rough night and they were swamped...well ok, so then that leaves me wondering why their own delivery guy had to come back twice (with food in hand) for 2 wrong deliveries and how come 2 other customers had their large orders done wrong as well. It seems like a pattern easily identified with 1 long, long visit.  Careless and lack of attention to the ticket.  I go to Wings Over Springfield, I've even been to Wings Over Hartford. These places serve good food. WOW or Wings Over Westfield needs a complete overhaul in signage, communication and service!!! However, I'll settle for just plain accuracy of giving me what I order the first time, not 45 minutes later...

Summary: The wings are usually very tasty when they arrive on time and are the correct items that were ordered. However, this restaurant's employees have very inconsistent customer service, no sense of time or accountability, and the management has poor problem resolution skills.  We are a large hospital and frequently order large quantities of food as a group ($75+). We are known to tip extremely well even when the food takes 3+ hours to be delivered. The food usually arrives missing an individual order, or with the wrong item(s), or without extra fries or dressing which was ordered extra at additional cost. The Wings staff have a poor sense of time and accountability. They will usually tell us the food will arrive in 45-60 minutes, and when we call an hour after ordering, they will tell us an additional 30-45 minutes. This creates an issue for us, as our break times are squeduled and we could act accordingly if we knew what time the food was actually expected to be delivered. When it does arrive, usually missing an item, it is difficult to get the correct item delivered. The person whose individual order was not correct has to call and argue with the Wings staff in order to get the correct order delivered, usually after another hour has gone by.  Whoever orders the food for the group usually knows to ask for "someone with more experience" to take the order as the girl who usually takes orders over the phone has no ability to accurately take the order. This seems to be an issue the Wings management is well aware of.  Tonight, 3/29/15, 3 hospital staff placed an order together. The order was called in at 4:25 pm, with an ETA of 45 minutes to an hour according to the Wings staff who took the order. After an hour, at 5:30, one of us called to check on the order. After being placed on hold for 15 minutes, Wings staff informed the hospital employees that the (delivery) order was taken incorrectly and was sitting at Wings ready for pickup. The Wings staff stated they would deliver it 'immediately', with an ETA of 6:15-6:30. At 6:30, hospital staff called Wings again to check on the food. At this point all of our meal breaks were over. The Wings staff member who answered the phone informed us that they had "decided not to deliver the order", and that "the general manager tried to call you several times". The weekend manager at the Westfield Wings location had no explanation or apology for this. We then called general manager, who had no knowledge of this issue and stated she had not tried to call anyone. She was gracious, and acknowledged the ongoing issues with the manager and order accuracy at the Westfield location. The food (ordered at 4:25 pm) finally arrived at 7:00 pm.
